      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1-2">
		Seventh year of Kampavarman.
	</p>
        <p n="2-3">
		Handwriting of the members of the assembly of Maṇali, a hamlet of Tiruvoṟṟiyūr.
	</p>
        <p n="3-5">
		The gold that Vēmpaṉ Kuṇuṅkaṉ Ammaṉ <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Iṟaiyāṉ Cēri in Mayilārppu gave for a glorious for the Mahādeva of Tiruvoṟṟiyūr, <supplied reason="subaudible">that is,</supplied> fifteen <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s of gold ..., we are bound to take it.
	</p>
        <p n="5-8">With this gold, we have become those who will ...
	</p>
        <p n="8-9">
		...
	</p>
        <p n="10-11">
		If failing, we have become those who will incur a fine of eight and a half <foreign>kāṇam</foreign>s, daily, at the <foreign>dharmāsana</foreign>.
	</p>
